President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday assured that everything was being done to rescue the students abducted from the Government Girls Technical College, Dapchi in Yobe State, saying more troops and surveillance aircraft were being deployed to the area for a 24-hour surveillance. The president in a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity Malam Garba Shehu, described the incident as a national disaster, and said he shared the pains of the parents. “When I received the devastating news, I immediately dispatched a high-level delegation on a fact-finding visit. I also instructed the security agencies to deploy in full and not spare any effort.” “The entire country stands as one with the girls’ families, the government and the people of Yobe State, and we share your pain. We pray that our gallant armed forces will locate and safely return your missing daughters,” he said.